WHEN A SITE LETS YOU UPLOAD A PICTURE .PNG , .JPEG, etc. Try these tricks to bypass the filter.

First try sending lots of requests via burp to see where the filter is blocking your file.

Here are some techniques.

If filter only allows files ending in .PNG, .JPEG, etc. Try adding a double file extension.

If the Content-Type header on image must be an image. Try opening up imagine in vim and adding code into it.
